      <hedline>
        <hl1>Standardizing the Standards</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Let's not be disingenuous about why we subject our children to standardized testing: we do it for the money it brings into districts that ''perform'' well (Ann Hulbert, May 27). When the funds roll in, property values rise, parents are happy and teachers gain job security.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Let's not be disingenuous about why we subject our children to standardized testing: we do it for the money it brings into districts that ''perform'' well (Ann Hulbert, May 27). When the funds roll in, property values rise, parents are happy and teachers gain job security.</p>
        <p>Maureen Tuthill</p>
        <p>Willington, Conn.</p>
